@Comment:	Time is 0:05
@Comment:	Chi and Mot sit on the couch. Chi leans back and Mot holds one side of the book , helps turn the pages and looks over Chi's shoulder. Chi leaves out words as he reads , but is reasonably fluent , indicating that he is not only relying on text (as Mot suggests at the beginning that he might read by memory). he stumbles over some words (especially at the end when he's getting tired) , and Mot helps by repeating the word before , by getting him to sound the problem word out , or by providing the word. Once after Mot provides a word , Chi whines <don't tell> and Mot says <but I want to help you>. Chi swallows the ends of words and phrases so that some hungry refrains can barely be heard.
